<Link id="l00286" /><CodeLine lineNumber="286"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00287" /><CodeLine lineNumber="287"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Extend the generic ELFStreamer class so that it can emit mapping symbols at</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00288" /><CodeLine lineNumber="288"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// the appropriate points in the object files. These symbols are defined in the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00289" /><CodeLine lineNumber="289"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// AArch64 ELF ABI:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00290" /><CodeLine lineNumber="290"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    infocenter.arm.com/help/topic/com.arm.doc.ihi0056a/IHI0056A&#95;aaelf64.pdf</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00291" /><CodeLine lineNumber="291"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00292" /><CodeLine lineNumber="292"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// In brief: $x or $d should be emitted at the start of each contiguous region</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00293" /><CodeLine lineNumber="293"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// of A64 code or data in a section. In practice, this emission does not rely</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00294" /><CodeLine lineNumber="294"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// on explicit assembler directives but on inherent properties of the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00295" /><CodeLine lineNumber="295"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// directives doing the emission (e.g. &quot;.byte&quot; is data, &quot;add x0, x0, x0&quot; an</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00296" /><CodeLine lineNumber="296"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// instruction).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00297" /><CodeLine lineNumber="297"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00298" /><CodeLine lineNumber="298"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// As a result this system is orthogonal to the DataRegion infrastructure used</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00299" /><CodeLine lineNumber="299"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// by MachO. Beware!</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00300" /><CodeLine lineNumber="300" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/anonymous-namespace-aarch64elfstreamer-cpp-/aarch64elfstreamer"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">class </span><span class="doxyHighlight"><a href="/docs/api/classes/anonymous-namespace-aarch64elfstreamer-cpp-/aarch64elfstreamer/#ab3c1d7ab672f0bd15bc00752eb7f8c4d">AArch64ELFStreamer</a> : </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">public</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcelfstreamer/#aec09c5b9322b90f034d51bd3c0903563">MCELFStreamer</a> &#123;</span></CodeLine>
